69th Legislature 2025 SB 421.1
1 SENATE BILL NO. 421
2 INTRODUCED BY E. BOLDMAN
3
4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING LAWS RELATED TO RESIDENTIAL RENTAL
5 APPLICATION FEES; WAIVING CHARGES FOR OR REQUIRING THE REFUND OF PORTIONS OF
6 RESIDENTIAL RENTAL APPLICATION FEES; ALLOWING CERTAIN COSTS TO BE DEDUCTED;
7 PROVIDING FOR A CIVIL ACTION IF AN APPLICATION FEE IS WRONGFULLY WITHHELD; PROVIDING
8 DEFINITIONS; AND PROVIDING AN IMMEDIATE EFFECTIVE DATE AND AN APPLICABILITY DATE.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Application fees -- credit checks -- reimbursement -- deduction of
13 costs. (1) A landlord or manager of a residential premises that requires an application fee prior to the rental of
14 the residential premises shall reimburse the application fee to the applicant within 20 days if the applicant does
15 not become a party to a signed rental agreement for the residential premises or on the date that the applicant
16 does not become a party to a rental agreement that has the same effect as if it had been signed pursuant to 70-
17 24-204. The landlord or manager of the residential premises may deduct out-of-pocket costs from the refund as
18 provided in subsection (3). Alternatively, the landlord or manager may accept a credit check, criminal
19 background check, or any application information as provided by the applicant within the prior 6 months, as
20 provided in subsection (2), and waive the application fee.
21 (2) Credit checks or criminal background checks performed by a landlord or manager must be
22 provided to the applicant within 7 days and remain valid for 6 months. Credit checks or criminal background
23 checks performed by a landlord or manager must identify the date of the credit check or criminal background
24 check and the name of the landlord or manager. The fee for credit checks or criminal background checks may
25 not exceed the cost to the landlord or manager of the credit check or criminal background check. Valid credit
26 checks or criminal background checks must be accepted by all landlords or managers and may not be
27 deducted as costs by more than one landlord or manager of a residence.
28 (3) If the application fee includes costs pertaining to specific services, the applicant must be given
